column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Warm- sunny- calm- 3" of rain past 3 days
Sunny- few clouds- calm water- 35 mph winds yesterday
Beautiful calm- sunny day.  No clouds- you cannot swim in the lake due to the algae.
A little overcast- lake is calm.- Assumed time was 12:00.
Sunny day- slight breeze- no clouds.
Day is sunny and clear- then cloudy and snow flurries- back to sunny.
Too cold to swim.  Ice off 4/15/94.  Very strong winds until today.  Partly sunny day.  Wood ducks + swallows back today.
Sunny- breezy day.  Two loons on the lake.
Clear + sunny with slight breeze.  Doe + fawn drinking other side of lake.
Clear sunny skies with slight breeze.
Sunny + calm.  Lake has turned over.
Sunny calm day.  If you go swimming you come out of the water with brown clinging to your body hairs + suit.
Beautiful sunny day with slight breeze.
Sunny day with a slight breeze.
Very calm- slightly overcast- 1.7" rain yesterday.
Overcast till 11 a.m.- then calm and sunny.
Water very dirty.  Partly sunny + cloudy.  Two eagles circling point.
Too muddy for swimming.  Sunny- few clouds- slight breeze.
Clear- sunny day.  Water lilies are starting to come up.  Some tree pollen are floating on water.
Beautiful sunny day.  Few clouds and slight breeze.
Very hot + sunny with no breeze.
Sunny-breezy day.  Prior water temp. 86 degrees- today 70 degrees.
Warm- sunny day.  No clouds- slight breeze.
Come out of the water and all the hair on your body is brown!
Clear sunny day- light breeze.  Today brown algae again clinging to body hair.
Sunny day-4 days after we got 5" rain.
And too cold.  Beautiful- sunny + slightly breezy.  Thunderstorms at 5 a.m.  Seagulls on lake.
Too cold to swim.  Sunny calm day.  1.5" rain yesterday.
Sunny- calm day- lots of rain before today.  Last reading for 1995.
Ice off May 7. first year lake ever froze out.
Beautiful warm sunny day. lake very calm.
Some pine pollen on lake. since freeze out- no loons- eagles or herons.
Partly cloudy. reading taken after 5 days rain.
Hot- sunny day. Two loons are back on lake.
Today weather is sunny- few clouds. great blue heron working the shoreline.
Beautiful day after 6 days of rain + cold. five loons on lake + mother northern ( ) and 10 babies.
Sunny warm day. eagle soaring overhead.
Cool- sunny day. lake level down some.
First reading for 1997.  Sunny- calm day.
Beautiful sunny day- no breeze.  Lots of bugs.
Sunny with slight breeze.  Heavy storms 2 days before reading.
Rain in the morning- sun in the pm- lake very dark.
When you come out of the water- your suit and skin are covered with reddish brown.
Sunny. nice day after early am thunder storms.
Sunny calm.  Water lilies in bloom.
Hot and sunny.  Kingfisher diving for small fish.
Warm no wind some clouds.  Very dry weather.
Sunny some clouds some wind. still dry.
Cloudy no wind. water temp. 70 degrees.
Clear sunny. 1/2" rain on Saturday.  Trees in color.  No water coming in lake.
Sunny warm no clouds and little wind.  6 ducks 1 eagle.
Beautiful- calm- sunny. 3 loons on lake.  Pollen from popple trees floating in water.  Beaver have the outlet dammed up- reason for lake being high.
Warm- sunny with slight breeze.  2 Canada geese + 3 goslings- 2 loons.  Lake still high even though the outlet has been opened.
Pt cloudy- calm.  Water lilies are up.  Doe + 2 fawns at waters edge.
Warm sunny with some clouds- light breeze.  One eagle- 2 geese- only 2 goslings left.
Cloudy- cool day.  There has been a lot of rain in the past week.
Weather cleared up in the pm + became sunny- warm- some clouds.  Still getting a lot of rain.
Sunny- clear day- no clouds. Water very dark. No activity on or around lake.
Quite clear- sunny with slight breeze from N.  Some algae starting to appear.
3 deer in water.  1 eagle swooped down + took fish out of water.  Clear- sunny.
Beautiful day.  Saw 1 eagle- 2 loons + 1 blue heron.
Clear- sunny day. 2 kingfishers on lake.
A quiet day on the lake. no wind- no clouds- lots of sun.
Sunny day- one loon- two geese with two goslings- one wood duck- and beavers have outlet damned up.
Five otters on one eagle.  Outlet damned up.  Weather has been rainy for last two weeks.  Got this reading in before clouded over.
Deer in water.  Cloudy day.  Outlet is open.
Sunny day with a few clouds.  One loon- four geese on lake.  Week has been cold with drizzle.
Finally a sunny day and no rain.  Saw two loons- one king fisher and one eagle.
Sun out until reading was taken.  Geese have left except for one that has been maimed.
Clear sunny day with a little wind.  One goose has a broken wing- two loons- and two geese on lake.
Two loons and four geese.  Sunny day.
Sunny day after one week of rain.  Saw two loons and one eagle.
Sunny day- the lake is calm- and no wildlife.
Sunny- warm day with a slight breeze- and the water temperature is 78 degrees.  One loon- one eagle- and one osprey.
Calm- sunny- and still day.  Three deer drinking and one loon.
Sunny day with a slight breeze.
Sunny and calm with few clouds.
Very hot and sunny day.  There are two loons on the lake.
There are two loons.  Sunny and calm day.
Calm- clear- and sunny day.  There are two loons on the lake.
Clear- sunny day with some wind.  Saw one loon.
Sunny day.  Lots of friendly flies- lots of dragon flies- 2 loons- and 1 heron.
Very hot- humid day.  2 eagles and 1 loon.
Sunny with few clouds.  1 eagle and 1 crane.
Sunny- calm day.  2 loons on lake and 1 eagle on top of tree.
Warm- sunny day.  2 loons on lake.
2 loons and 1 osprey on lake. Sunny with slight breeze.
1 blue heron. 2 loons. Deer drinking from shore. Clear sunny day- no wind.
Sun shining and 2 loons on lake.
Sunny day with slight breeze. 2 loons on lake.
Warm and sunny. 1 mallard drake and 2 loons.
Beautiful sunny day.  2 loons on lake.
Sunny day- slight breeze.  Saw 2 loons- 1 adult eagle- 2 young eagles and one fawn.
Nice sunny warm day- after a week of cool- rainy weather and no sun.  2 loons and (4 adult- 8 young) 2 families of geese.
Cool- sunny day- 2 loons on lake.
A clear- sunny day.  3 loons on lake.
Sunny day- slight breeze.  Few clouds- 3 loons.
4 northern ducks- 2 loons- 1 eagle.  Sunny with few clouds.
2 loons- 1 beaver- 1 eagle.  Lake low as they put in a new culvert at the outlet.
Lake riled up due to 2 days of high winds.  Saw 2 eagles- 1 crane.
Beautiful sunny day.  Lake is calm.  2 geese on lake.
Sunny- clear and slight breeze.  2 loons.
Sunny day- after a day of rain and wind.  2 loons still on lake.
lake covered with pollen- 2 loons- sunny day
clear sunny day after night of stormy weather
clear sunny day- two loons and two eagles
one loon on lake- clear sunny day
clear sunny day- some clouds- 2 loons on lake
Beautiful sunny day. No clouds- 2 loons- one duck on lake. 1 heron on shore.  Eagle flying overhead
Nice day.  Had 2 inches of rain two days ago.  No wildlife on or around lake.
weeds starting to fill shallow areas
cloudy- calm- recent heavy boat traffic
dead weeds starting to settle down
sunny 90 degrees F- no fain for more than a week
partly cloudy- 78 degrees F- ripple- recent hot spell and heavy rain
mostly sunny- 74 degrees F- ripple. Sandra Wickman of the WDNR came along to instruct for water samples and temperature recording
72 degrees- partly cloudy- light breeze. Saw two loons- Blue Heron- and a mallard drake swimming with a Canada Goose. Ice only off for a week
79 degrees- sunny- lots of boats out
73 degrees- mostly sunny- windy- turtles on floating mats.
74 degees- partly cloudy- slight breeze- pair of loons but no chicks.
70 degrees- cloudy- light breeze- four people fishing- two in bass boat
53 degrees- clear sky- flat calm- some people on lake.
53 dgrees- sunny- few high clouds- no one on lake.
sunny- breezy- 69F- pair Buffle Heads- one Canada goose- one loon- five turtles- one Blue Heron- five fishermen
partly cloudy- light breeze- blue heron- pontoon boat- two paddle boats
sunny- light breeze- algae near shore in shallows
light breeze- partly cloudy- hazy- 75F- pair of loons- no chicks
sunny- light breeze- 72F- two turtles- one beaver
70 degrees F. Mostly cloudy- ripple- two small turtles- Blue Heron- pair of mallards- one canadian goose
few clouds- 85 degrees- lite breeze- grey tree frogs singing- blue heron- two people brushing on island
mostly sunny- 82 degrees- humid- lite breeze- snapping turtle
